line_1: In Lust perhaps you others have excell'd,
line_2: And made all Whores that possibly would yield;

line_1: Her own Meander's art almost excell'd!
line_2: With jealous fear declining Greece beheld

line_1: In arms who triumph'd; or in arts excell'd;
line_2: Proud names, who once the reins of empire held;

line_1: Speak, and confess thy art excell'd.
Here Moliere, first of comick wits, excell'd
Moses eclips'd, and Jesse's Son excell'd.
line_2: And the astonish'd World in Me beheld

line_1: What thro' the whole Creation has excell'd:
line_2: Amass'd in Man there justly is beheld
" I thought when you my fair beheld,

line_1: That all your mossy Caves are here excell'd.
line_2: NOW blush, CALYPSO; 'tis but just to yield,

line_1: His Wisdom there the wisest Peers excell'd;
line_2: His Valour more surpass'd 'em in the Field.
